video chair exercises senior fitness yoga for seniors";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/6c/94/a6/6c94a64e64218e5e1050fded289e2a40.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTW6TqhOoE1lu6mXpmbFNceDVuXcr-rf-P-Nw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:2304;s:6:"height";i:1842;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://sk.pinterest.com/pin/466615211398498197/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"sk.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:64:{i:0;s:54:"A few benefits of chair exercises for seniors include.";i:1;s:195:"Improved flexibility and range of motion Decreased joint pain and stiffness Improved muscle strength and balance Increased blood circulation Elevated mood and concentration Lowered stress levels.";i:2;s:110:"Push a sturdy chair against a wall so the back is to the wall and the chair isnt at risk of sliding or moving.";i:3;s:60:"Stand facing the chair feet roughly shoulder-distance apart.";i:4;s:72:"Press your hips back and bend your knees to enter a half-squat position.";i:5;s:101:"Place both hands firmly on the chairs seat arms fully extended and palms aligned under the shoulders.";i:6;s:75:"Sit comfortably at the edge of the chair without feeling like falling over.";i:7;s:57:"Keep the back straight and the core abs and lumbar tight.";i:8;s:76:"Place both hands at the sides of the chair and grip the seat to keep stable.";i:9;s:72:"Place both feet far out in front of the body and point the toes forward.";i:10;s:95:"Seated in a chair with good posture hold a ball with both hands slightly in front of your body.";i:11;s:123:"Squeeze the ball to activate the finger joints then slowly press the ball with both hands as if trying to deflate the ball.";i:12;s:38:"Hold for 4 seconds and slowly release.";i:13;s:22:"Repeat the exercise 8.";i:14;s:84:"Sit slightly forward in a chair with your feet under you about shoulder-width apart.";i:15;s:92:"Lean slightly forward with the back straight and slowly stand up extending the arms forward.";i:16;s:222:"Toe taps chair exercise is one more exercise for seniors and it strengthens the muscles in your lower front and the rear of the leg which are used for several day-to-day activities like climbing or getting down the stairs.";i:17;s:66:"Below are steps to be followed for performing this chair exercise.";i:18;s:109:"These stretches are perfect for seniors who cant move around easily or for those who want to start off small.";i:19;s:46:"All of these exercises can be done in a chair.";i:20;s:64:"You can choose to stand for some of them if you prefer to do so.";i:21;s:43:"Raise your arms out so your body forms a T.";i:22;s:47:"Move your arms in small circles moving forward.";i:23;s:20:"Do this eight times.";i:24;s:96:"The decision to want to do chair exercises can only be made final by the seniors who will do it.";i:25;s:102:"You cannot force your wishes and also your family or from medical staff to seniors do chair exercises.";i:26;s:92:"Because if forced continuously seniors can get stress and this is not good for their health.";i:27;s:44:"Why chair exercises are helpful for seniors.";i:28;s:66:"A major benefit of chair exercises is the reduced risk of falling.";i:29;s:94:"Its also a great way for seniors with limited mobility to get the health benefits of exercise.";i:30;s:119:"Chair exercises can be just as challenging as regular standing workouts especially for upper body or abdominal muscles.";i:31;s:140:"While many seniors may not be able to get that hoop going at their waist they can try it on their arms smaller hoops are handy for this too.";i:32;s:86:"Be sure to have Teresa Brewers 1958 song The Hula Hoop Song on hand to get them going.";i:33;s:67:"Bending over to pick up the fallen hula hoop is also good exercise.";i:34;s:63:"Sit at the edge of your chair with your feet flat on the floor.";i:35;s:30:"Flex your foot up towards you.";i:36;s:31:"Raise your leg up a few inches.";i:37;s:42:"Perform these steps with the opposite leg.";i:38;s:73:"Jumping jacks is by far the best exercise that strengthens heart muscles.";i:39;s:57:"This is known to be one of the most challenging ones too.";i:40;s:61:"This cardio activity is not safe and doable for many seniors.";i:41;s:115:"However there is an alternative as well which is called seated jumping jacks and it is completely safe for seniors.";i:42;s:15:"Hook Loop Toss.";i:43;s:111:"Set up a hook and loop target for residents to play a game of tar grip toss where the balls stay on the target.";i:44;s:131:"For each round of the game have residents toss their tar grip balls to see who can land theirs closest to the center of the target.";i:45;s:181:"Chair Exercises for Seniors Medically reviewed by Gregory Minnis DPT Chair exercises are great for everyone including seniors and anyone looking for ways to stay active as they age.";i:46;s:53:"Seated exercise classes are some of our most popular.";i:47;s:132:"The gentle chair-based exercises are great for improving your posture and balance and are suitable for people with reduced mobility.";i:48;s:82:"Some classes introduce resistance bands and hand weights for muscle strengthening.";i:49;s:104:"Water aerobics exercises improve your strength flexibility and balance with minimal stress on your body.";i:50;s:179:"Like water aerobics chair yoga is a low-impact form of exercise that improves muscle strength mobility balance and flexibility all of which are crucial health aspects for seniors.";i:51;s:88:"Seated core exercises for seniors are easier for people who have problems with mobility.";i:52;s:85:"These exercises can be performed while you are at work or sitting in a chair at home.";i:53;s:136:"With the right type of core exercise seniors may be able to regain some of their mobility and start exercising from a standing position.";i:54;s:38:"Hand Squeeze With Chair Exercise Ball.";i:55;s:83:"If you are searching for a really simple exercise then the hand squeeze is for you.";i:56;s:128:"It is one of the easiest seated chair exercises for seniors with a chair exercise ball that can be performed virtually anywhere.";i:57;s:35:"You can perform it by using a ball.";i:58;s:55:"This move helps to contract your arm muscles and chest.";i:59;s:127:"Those cardiovascular benefits help increase endurance making it easier to perform difficult moves for longer stretches of time.";i:60;s:79:"The key is to make seated exercise a regular part of the senior living routine.";i:61;s:110:"Many seniors add chair exercises to their daily routine to ease the aches and pains associated with arthritis.";i:62;s:112:"Chair exercises are great for everyone including seniors and anyone looking for ways to stay active as they age.";i:63;s:70:"Learn about some seated and standing chair exercises for seniors here.";}}